Frequently asked questions 

How do i get my compiler to work ?

[b]step 1[/b] Right click your compiler.bat and click edit

[b]step 2[/b] Delete every thing and  replace with this

[code]

CLS

:index

CLS
@COLOR 0c
@Title my compiler by eekz

@ECHO By eekz

@ECHO -

@ECHO Type 1 to run the server

@ECHO Type 2 to compile	

@ECHO Type 3 to load the mopar client	

@ECHO Type 4 to load hamachi	

@ECHO Type 5 to load no-ip	

@SET option=

@ECHO - 

@ECHO off

SET /p option=What Do You Choose? 

if %option%==1 goto run

if %option%==2 goto c

if %option%==3 goto mc

if %option%==4 goto h

if %option%==5 goto n

CLS

goto info
:run

CLS
COLOR 0c
@echo off
title Run server
java -Xmx1024m -cp .;./jython.jar;./MySql/mysql-connector-java-3.0.17-ga-bin.jar server

CLS

goto info
:c

CLS
@echo off
Title Compiler
color 0c
echo Compiling...
"C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0\bin\javac" *.java -nowarn *.java
color 0c
SET /p option=Go Back To Start? 

if %option%==yes goto index	



pause 
CLS

goto info
:mc

CLS
@echo off
Title mopar loader
color 0c
echo Loading...
"C:\Program Files\MoparScape\MoparScape.jar
color 0c
SET /p option=Go Back To Start? 

if %option%==yes goto index	


CLS

goto info
:h

CLS
COLOR 0c
title Hamachi Starter
@echo Starting Hamachi...
"C:\Program Files\Hamachi\hamachi.exe"
SET /p option=Go Back To Start? 

if %option%==yes goto index	


CLS

goto info
:n

CLS
COLOR 0c
title No-Ip Starter
@echo Starting No-Ip...
"C:\Program Files\No-IP\duc20.exe"
SET /p option=Go Back To Start? 

if %option%==yes goto index	


CLS
[/code]

[b]step 3 [/b] Change the [code]jdk1.6.0[/code] in the text i just gave you to your version

[b]step 4[/b]  Save it and close

